<subSubSection pageId="210" pageNumber="211" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="210.[151,1437,438,1978]" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[549,709,1086,1113]" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">Frigate Tuna</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity box="[769,843,1087,1113]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" unit="cm" value="61.0">61 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[863,928,1087,1114]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.096" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" unit="in" value="24.0">24 in</quantity>
) TL (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller and Lea" box="[1000,1250,1087,1113]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" refId="ref302113" refString="Miller, D. J. &amp; Lea, R. N. (1972) Guide to the coastal marine fishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 157." type="book" year="1972">Miller and Lea 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Circumglobal; Huntington Beach (Personal communication: Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History Fish Collection, Los Angeles, California), and Santa Catalina Island, southern California to 
<collectingCountry box="[1064,1125,1159,1185]" name="Chile" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pequeno" box="[1141,1309,1159,1185]" firstAuthor="Pequeno" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref311468" refString="Pequeno R., G. (1989) Peces de Chile lista sistematica revisada y comentada. Revista de Biologia Marina y Oceanografia, 24, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1989">Pequeño 1989</bibRefCitation>
), including Gulf of California (
<bibRefCitation author="Robertson and Allen" box="[427,736,1194,1221]" firstAuthor="Robertson" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" refId="ref316799" refString="Robertson, D. R. and Allen, G. R. (2015) Shorefishes of the Tropical Eastern Pacific: an Information System. Version 2.0 (2008). Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute, Balboa. http: // biogeodb. stri. si. edu / sftep / en / pages" type="url" year="2015">Robertson and Allen 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and Islas Galápagos (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller and Lea" box="[1005,1253,1195,1221]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" refId="ref302113" refString="Miller, D. J. &amp; Lea, R. N. (1972) Guide to the coastal marine fishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 157." type="book" year="1972">Miller and Lea 1972</bibRefCitation>
). The record of this species from the southern Kuril Islands in 
<bibRefCitation author="Savinykh" box="[746,936,1231,1257]" firstAuthor="Savinykh" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="18 - 27" refId="ref320217" refString="Savinykh, V. F. (1998) Nekton composition of near-surface waters of the subarctic front zone in the northwest part of the Pacific Ocean according to the data of drift-net catches. Journal of Ichthyology, 38, 18 - 27." type="journal article" year="1998">Savinykh (1998)</bibRefCitation>
appears to be in error and was changed to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Risso" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[198,339,1267,1293]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scombridae" genus="Auxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rochei">
<emphasis box="[198,339,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">Auxis rochei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Parin" box="[377,522,1267,1293]" firstAuthor="Parin" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="40" refId="ref309544" refString="Parin, N. V. (2003) An annotated catalogue of fish-like vertebrates and fishes of the seas of Russia and adjacent countries: Part 3. Orders Perciformes (excluding suborders Gobioidei, Zoarcoidei and Stichaeoidei) and Tetraodontiformes. Journal of Ichthyology, 43, S 1 - S 40." type="journal article" year="2003">Parin (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. Neritic and oceanic epipelagic; depth: surface to 
<quantity box="[1089,1161,1267,1293]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" unit="m" value="200.0">200 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1177,1248,1266,1294]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.999488" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" unit="ft" value="656.0">656 ft</quantity>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Robertson and Allen" firstAuthor="Robertson" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" refId="ref316713" refString="Robertson, D. R. &amp; Allen, G. R. (2002) Shorefishes of the tropical eastern Pacific: an information system. CD-ROM. Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute, Balboa, Panama." type="book" year="2002">Robertson and Allen 2002</bibRefCitation>
). The eastern Pacific form is recognized as the subspecies 
<taxonomicName authority="Collette and Aadland 1996" authorityName="Collette and Aadland" authorityYear="1996" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scombridae" genus="Auxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="thazard" subSpecies="brachydorax">
<emphasis box="[988,1292,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="210" pageNumber="211">Auxis thazard brachydorax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Collette and Aadland" firstAuthor="Collette" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="423 - 441" refId="ref271244" refString="Collette, B. B. &amp; Aadland, C. R. (1996) Revision of the frigate tunas (Scombridae, Auxis), with descriptions of two new subspecies from the eastern Pacific. Fishery Bulletin, 94, 423 - 441." type="journal article" year="1996">Collette and Aadland 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Collette" box="[370,529,1339,1365]" firstAuthor="Collette" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" refId="ref271181" refString="Collette, B. B. (2003) Family Scombridae Rafinesque 1815. Mackerels, tunas, and bonitos. California Academy of Sciences Annotated Checklists of Fishes, No. 19." type="book" year="2003">Collette 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
